node.text: I sent him a nude last night, and then had 25-30 people text him at the same time this morning saying some form of, “DID YOU MEAN TO POST THAT”? There’s a lot of ups and downs in this video but if you ever want to see Jason mad, here’s your chance. It doesn’t happen often.. but when it does, it’s scary. Hahah I love you babe thanks for being a good sport. 🤣 #aprilfools

node.title: Please join me on this emotional journey for my April fools joke on Jason.

node.text:
This year at @dewedit we have one motto: DEW YOU!
What I want for you all is to be unafraid to be authentically yourself.

We also have a few goals we are working on at Dew this year.
1. Launch our dewedit.com website ✔️
2. Making our way to environmentally sustainable packaging.
3. Build a loyalty program for my scrunchie gang.
 
Would love to hear your thoughts/feedback on the new website!

node.text: You were chaotic, magical, pivotal, and unforgettable. Ending the year with covid wasn’t ideal, but I’ve never had a better perspective on what matters in life. Im proud of this year. I released two songs, had meaningful podcasts, launched new wine, grew my businesses, and won the mirrorball. I was humbled in diverse conversations, and I pushed myself more than I ever have. All I can ask for in 2021 is time with loved ones. I cannot tell you how much I miss my family. Happy New Year everyone. What’s 1 thing you’re bringing into 2021? Jason and I have agreed on the word, perspective. #2021  #HNY

node.text: This was when I found out I was going on @dancingabc . It feels like yesterday and now I’m heading into the FINALE. It’s been a freakin RIDE. A journey if you will.  One I have wanted for 5 years. I have cried tears of happiness, sadness, tears of body injuries and pain. I have laughed, I have learned, I have felt insecure, and not good enough. I have compared myself to others, and then reminded myself that this is where I’m supposed to be.  I feel so strong, and have so much gratitude for my body right now. I have grown more than I thought was possible through this. This is my ACTUAL dream. This shouldn’t be easy. I have always wanted to be a dancer, and now I feel like I am one. I feel good enough. Thank you Artem for helping me with that. And to this guy (Jason), who has been here by my side the whole time. Making me dinner when I come home, rubbing my disgusting blistered feet, hugging me while I cry, celebrating me when I nail it... All while building his own empire, and taking care of the dogs. Thank you. This process has been hard. Hours and hours a day 7 days a week of mentally physically draining days. It takes a solid partnership in the dance studio for sure, but it also takes a strong relationship at home that makes you feel supported. Jason has done nothing but support my dream from this night, to the finale. Thank you J. I love you, your motivation pump up speeches, and your heart so much. Finale. Here we come. Dreams really do come true. @jason_tartick @dancingabc @theartemc #dwts @chrisbharrison #TheBachelorette

node.text:
To get a perfect score on both dances this week felt surreal! This redemption dance felt GOOOOD. I felt more controlled and powerful than my first Paso Doble. I have to say, it is so rewarding to put everything you have into something, and to see the hard work pay off! My Paso Doble was for you guys. I hope I can encourage you to give it your all, to put the work in and to fight for the things you want to achieve in life. It’s a good feeling when you see the growth and results! And once again… thanks for all the love, support and VOTES! One week to goooo…… #DWTS

node.text: It happened!! I got a perfect score, and it couldn’t have come at a better time. I’ve been feeling a little defeated, and exhausted. Seeing 10’s across the board was soooo encouraging, validating, and gave us the momentum we needed to dance in THE SEMI FINALS. What. How!?? Oh wait I know how. A sweet little combo of dedication, passion and your VOTES. Thank you. Thank you. Thank you for allowing me to make it through each week by voting. I love you guys!!! Also. Thank you Artem for pushing me and knowing my potential @dancingabc #dwts

node.text:
That I’m havin’ a good time is an UNDERSTATEMENT. I’m not going to lie, I was terrified at the possibility of going home last week. It shook my confidence. I tried to go into this week remembering that I’m here for a reason. I’m here because I believe in myself and never gave up on a dream. I did it! But to be honest, I couldn’t have done it without YOUR VOTES. Between my passion, Artems’ patience, his choreography, and our drive to stay, your votes always get us through. We wouldn’t be here without you. Thank you for believing in us!! Thank you. 
@theartemc @dancingabc #dwts #willyouacceptthisdance

node.text:
I always wanna toss up the ol vitamin gummies and catch them in my mouth. Makes me feel cool. As you can see here it doesn’t always work out. Anywhoo . ➡️
K real talk, ever since I had covid back in December I am REALLY focusing on my immune health. Jason loves @bulletproof coffee, and he told me to try these vitamins from them. I’m PICKY with what I put in my bod. And these are incredible. No sugar, DELISH, science backed. These ADK vitamins have, you guessed it, A D and K vitamins. And so many of us are deficient in vitamin D amirite? You know I don’t throw things at you if I don’t try first. I’ve been taking these for 6 weeks now and they are chefs kiss 💋 #bulletproofpartner

node.text:
I can’t go out *cough* I’m sick…
Happy National white wine day! My Pinot Grigio is truly the most drinkable white wines out there. Notes of melon, citrus, and crisp apple. Pairs well with a mountain of laundry. Tell me your favorite wine pairing! I’m going to pin the top 3. Also to get your hands on a bottle head to my story! @spadeandsparrows #wine #NationalWhiteWine
